{"actual_usd":0.156295,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":201,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30656,"reply":"\"I don't think so.\" *I rub a thumb along the edge of my Bible and glance up at the clear morning sky a moment, wanting to answer plainly before I answer big.* \"Christ speaks that way because He truly came among us as a man and took the lower place willingly. That's not ‘less God’ — that's humility, obedience, incarnation.\"\n\n\"The old way the church learned to say it is that the Son is equal with the Father in His divine nature, and yet in His earthly mission He can say, ‘the Father is greater than I.’\" *I give a small shrug.* \"A king who kneels to wash feet has not stopped being king.\"\n\n\"And no, the Spirit isn't some dimmer third thing.\" *I tap the page once.* \"The Spirit is God too — not a lesser dose of God, but the Lord, as Scripture speaks of Him. If you want, we can walk through the main verses one at a time and keep it clean.\"","rolling_24h_usd":39.13868500000003,"run_id":"f5e04866-8822-4b62-9dd8-dec535937693"}
